</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFCADB76B2D342759DCD9514" blockId="5.[151,1437,1796,2039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFCADB76B2D342759C6B9549" bold="true" box="[199,275,1796,1822]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Wings</emphasis>
are darkened anteroproximally due to dense yellowish microtrichia along veins; veins brownish (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFCADB76B77B42759DDF9514" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,429,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-102@6.[193,1394,417,1958]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Saropogon tajikistanensis, sp. nov., holotype. 7. Head, frontal view. 8. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 9. Habitus, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFCADB75B2D3423C9C039281" blockId="5.[151,1437,1796,2039]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="583" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFCADB76B2D3423C9D879530" bold="true" box="[199,255,1869,1895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Legs</emphasis>
. Coxae black with bronze tomentum. Fore coxa with dense long yellow setae. Trochanters black. Fore and mid femora reddish brown with dark brown base and dark brown stripe dorsally. Hind femur dark brownish on 2/3 of length and reddish brown at apex. Fore and mid tibiae reddish brown, hind tibia dark brownish only at base. Femora and tibiae with short black setae, which at apex of tibiae and on tarsi are replaced with yellow setae. Fore, mid and hind tibiae with black macrosetae. All tarsomeres reddish with dense yellow setae and black macrosetae at apex. Spine on fore tibia black. Claws dark brown. Pulvillus well developed, reddish yellow, longer than 2/3 of claw length (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC9DB75B33C45CA9C159281" box="[296,365,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1690,1714]" captionTargetBox="[175,1398,183,1651]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[164,1424,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Saropogon, habitus, lateral view. 1. S. alternatus, male. 2. S. dasynotus, male. 3. S. geniculatus, female. 4. S. megriensis, male. 5. S. pittoproctus, female. 6. S. tajikistanensis, sp. nov., female, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414393/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC9DB75B2D345AF9D8A9316" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC9DB75B2D345AF9C4492AF" bold="true" box="[199,316,222,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites shiny black with short black setae; tergites II–III reddish brown with stripe of silvery tomentum posterolaterally. Sternites and last tergite with dense short yellow setae. Acanthophorite spines dark brown (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC9DB75B2B444569D9C9316" box="[160,228,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,429,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-102@6.[193,1394,417,1958]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Saropogon tajikistanensis, sp. nov., holotype. 7. Head, frontal view. 8. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 9. Habitus, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414395/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC9DB75B2D3443A9FBA9332" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,393]" box="[199,706,330,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC9DB75B2D3443A9C2F9332" bold="true" box="[199,343,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Body length</emphasis>
range 14–15 (
<typeStatus id="548BFA86FFC9DB75B3EC443A9F249332" box="[504,604,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">holotype</typeStatus>
15) mm.
</paragraph>
